<gtr:projectOverview xmlns:gtr="http://gtr.ukri.org/api"><gtr:projectComposition><gtr:collaborations/><gtr:leadResearchOrganisation url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/7ADE0AB2-1050-4241-987D-F3B1C3322E05"><gtr:id>7ADE0AB2-1050-4241-987D-F3B1C3322E05</gtr:id><gtr:name>NERC British Geological Survey</gtr:name><gtr:department>UNLISTED</gtr:department><gtr:address><gtr:line1>Kingsley Dunham Centre</gtr:line1><gtr:line2>Nicker Hill</gtr:line2><gtr:line3>Keyworth</gtr:line3><gtr:line4>Nottingham</gtr:line4><gtr:line5>Nottinghamshire</gtr:line5><gtr:postCode>NG12 5GG</gtr:postCode><gtr:region>East Midlands</gtr:region><gtr:country>United Kingdom</gtr:country></gtr:address><gtr:typeInd>RO</gtr:typeInd></gtr:leadResearchOrganisation><gtr:organisationRoles><gtr:organisationRole url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/7ADE0AB2-1050-4241-987D-F3B1C3322E05"><gtr:id>7ADE0AB2-1050-4241-987D-F3B1C3322E05</gtr:id><gtr:name>NERC British Geological Survey</gtr:name><gtr:address><gtr:line1>Kingsley Dunham Centre</gtr:line1><gtr:line2>Nicker Hill</gtr:line2><gtr:line3>Keyworth</gtr:line3><gtr:line4>Nottingham</gtr:line4><gtr:line5>Nottinghamshire</gtr:line5><gtr:postCode>NG12 5GG</gtr:postCode><gtr:region>East Midlands</gtr:region><gtr:country>United Kingdom</gtr:country></gtr:address><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>LEAD_RO</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:organisationRole></gtr:organisationRoles><gtr:personRoles><gtr:personRole url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/6B301714-EF85-41A6-8038-66BA9829E180"><gtr:id>6B301714-EF85-41A6-8038-66BA9829E180</gtr:id><gtr:firstName>Kenneth</gtr:firstName><gtr:surname>Lawrie</gtr:surname><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>PRINCIPAL_INVESTIGATOR</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole></gtr:personRoles><gtr:project url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/projects?ref=RES-192-27-0003"><gtr:id>2D36C379-C483-4E73-A1FF-0E2D51AF094D</gtr:id><gtr:title>Towards an integrated 'Geodata' system to support Glasgow City Council's regeneration and other infrastructure development activities</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Fellowship</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>RES-192-27-0003</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>This project aims to establish the scope and content of existing, but currently disconnected and often relatively inaccessible geoscience and other environmental subsurface data resources held by various Glasgow City Council (GCC) departments, and selected neighbouring local authorities. These resources, and their underpinning knowledge, will be identified and characterised initially by questionnaire, interview and report. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The project will then aim to propose a suite of structures, methodologies and processes which draw these resources together and make them readily, and potentially very visually, accessible. This will build upon pre-existing systems and 3D subsurface models to provide a holistic and integrated Local Authority-wide geoscience and geoenvironmental resource. This will better inform decision making under the various planning processes, in particular those underpinning major regeneration projects. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The sharing and communication of data and knowledge between GCC, neighbouring local authorities, and the British Geological Survey will be of multiple and mutual benefit. It will enable efficient two way value added data streams which will aid the responsiveness of the organisations. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The methodologies, processes and systems emanating from the project will have the broader potential to form templates for other local authorities to use in capturing, accessing, communicating and sharing geoscience, geoenvironmental and other vital datasets.&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2010-12-01</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2010-08-02</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>9753</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications/><gtr:identifiers><gtr:identifier type="RES">RES-192-27-0003</gtr:identifier><gtr:identifier type="RCUK">RES-192-27-0003</gtr:identifier></gtr:identifiers><gtr:healthCategories/><gtr:researchActivities/><gtr:researchSubjects><gtr:researchSubject><gtr:id>EBACD6D4-D1E5-4970-8BEC-7F4568EB26BA</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Development studies</gtr:text></gtr:researchSubject></gtr:researchSubjects><gtr:researchTopics><gtr:researchTopic><gtr:id>32A0976A-B577-4829-A940-9AB6B148F977</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Area &amp; Development Studies</gtr:text></gtr:researchTopic></gtr:researchTopics><gtr:rcukProgrammes/></gtr:project></gtr:projectComposition></gtr:projectOverview>